The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Lara: Sachin Bradman of modern era
                                                                                                                       7                                      Lara: Sachin Bradman of modern era
                      
	Dubai: Saluting the longevity of Sachin Tendulkar, West Indies great Brian Lara has described the Indian batting legend as the Don Bradman of the modern era but refused to the compare the two.         
	Lara, himself a legendary left-handed batsman, said that he was astonished by Tendulkars longevity.         
	I dont think there is any race. Both are great. Tendulkar has shown the world what he is capable of and his longevity in the game is something to be appreciated, Lara said.         
	More time he will spend playing, more records will tumble. The fact that someone can be there from the age of 16 and still at the age of 37 perform brilliantly, is something that I cherish more than anything else, he said.He is our periods Don Bradman. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
